	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName> <date>8 Dec 5617&#47;1857</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Revd. &#38; Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I should have replied earlier to yours<lb/> of <date>4<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> ulto. But have been confined to my bed since<lb/> the <date>6<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> and only left it yesterday.  I thank you for<lb/> yours and as soon as I can move about to raise<lb/> the funds for Books will do so.  I note what you say concerning <persName>Mr Gotthelf&#39;s</persName> remarks as to what<lb/> I owe on your account.  I understood from him that<lb/> he had settled up with you for my subscription<lb/> to the Occident some time ago and also for<lb/> the Bibles had&#58; however if you will oblige<lb/> me with a statement of what you conceive<lb/> my indebtedness to be&#44; I will thank you&#44; as I<lb/> shall then have something tangible to lay<lb/> before him.  On your reply I may explain<lb/> more fully.  Please attend to it.  Wishing you<lb/> many years of Long Life &#38; Health for the<lb/> benefit of our Holy Cause I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)">Truly Yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">A J H Bernal</persName></p>
				<p>P. S. There is a <persName>Revd. Dr. De Banco</persName><lb/> here candidate as Rab in the old <add>Hebrew</add> He claims to<lb/> be from <placeName>Hamburg</placeName> son of an Italian.  Has been<lb/> in the <placeName>States</placeName> ten years&#44; in <placeName>N.Y.</placeName>  and <placeName>N. O.</placeName> Did<lb/> you ever hear of him before&#63;  I did not.</p>
				<p>P.S. Altho&#39; the Commit have not made a final report on the<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Destructive</hi> Prayer Book of <persName>Wise</persName>&#44; yet by a<lb/> resolution of the School Directors&#44; it has been<lb/> adopted in their School.  Can nothing be done<lb/> to put a stop to such nefarious proceedings&#44; thus<lb/> poisoning the minds of youth.</p>
		</body>
